Mr. Atherton said@#%^&*9
CityFed will also mark its portfolio of high-yield corporate bonds@#%^&*9
to market@#%^&*9
as a result of federal legislation@#%^&*9
requiring@#%^&*9
that savings institutions divest themselves of such bonds.@#%^&*9
That action,@#%^&*10
CityFed said,@#%^&*10
will result in a charge against third-quarter results of approximately $30 million.@#%^&*10
CityFed also said@#%^&*11
it expects to shed its remaining mortgage loan origination operations outside its principal markets in New Jersey and Florida@#%^&*11
and, as a result, is taking a charge for discontinued operations.@#%^&*11
All these actions,@#%^&*12
Mr. Atherton said,@#%^&*12
will result in a loss of $125 million to $150 million for the third quarter.@#%^&*12
He added, however:@#%^&*13
"Depending on the resolution of certain accounting issues@#%^&*13
